        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(durable): add opt-in agent coordination kernel",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis replaces the cumulative implementation stack from #97468, #97469, and #97476 with one self-contained vertical slice for agent review.\n\nIt adds an opt-in native durable agent coordination kernel that records:\n\n- workflow runs, steps, events, refs, timers, signals, and child links;\n- agent-turn lifecycle checkpoints;\n- read-only Gateway coordination projection;\n- CLI inspection helpers;\n- subagent child-run recording and fan-in state.\n\nThe goal is not to replace Task Flow/background tasks/Workboard. This PR gives those surfaces a shared, bounded coordination ledger for restart-safe multi-agent work.\n\n## Reviewer Feedback Addressed\n\n- **No sidecar DB by default.** Durable tables now live in the canonical shared state database at `state/openclaw.sqlite` via `resolveOpenClawStateSqlitePath(...)`.\n- **Shared schema lifecycle.** The durable tables are added to `src/state/openclaw-state-schema.sql` and regenerated schema artifacts.\n- **Disabled by default.** Runtime hooks and Gateway reads require `OPENCLAW_DURABLE_WORKFLOWS` to be explicitly enabled.\n- **Disabled read is non-mutating.** `durable.coordination.get` returns disabled without opening/creating durable state; this has a regression test.\n- **No raw subagent task persistence.** Subagent coordination metadata stores ids, bounded labels/names, and `taskHash`; it no longer stores the raw `task` body.\n- **Reviewable stack.** This is one clean commit rebased onto current `main` instead of four cumulative PRs targeting `main`.\n- **No ledger-only operator controls.** The initial CLI surface is read-only inspection; cancel/retry/resume/signal write controls were removed until they can be wired to the live task/agent runtime contract.\n\n## User Impact\n\nThis targets the class of bugs where long-running or branching agent work becomes silent or hard to recover:\n\n- parent agent waits on subagents but cannot tell which child is still open;\n- one failed child should not block unrelated sibling completion;\n- gateway restart should not erase where a coordinated run was;\n- operators need a bounded timeline/projection instead of scraping sessions or plugin state.\n\n## Scope Boundaries\n\n- Feature is opt-in and experimental.\n- Normal chat turns are unchanged while the flag is off.\n- This does not add CLI write controls, retention/compaction, Postgres, or multi-worker leases.\n- This does not change Task Flow or Workboard semantics yet; it provides primitives they can project onto later.\n\n## Local Proof\n\nFocused runtime tests:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/durable/sqlite-store.test.ts src/durable/fan-in.test.ts src/durable/recovery.test.ts src/durable/executor.test.ts src/durable/coordination-projection.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/durable.test.ts src/durable/subagent.test.ts src/state/openclaw-state-db.test.ts\n\nUnit shard: 7 files passed, 31 tests passed, 1 skipped.\nGateway shard: 2 files passed, 4 tests passed.\n```\n\nType and architecture guards:\n\n```text\nnpm run tsgo:core\nnode scripts/check-kysely-guardrails.mjs\n```\n\nBoth passed. `check-kysely-guardrails` reported `Kysely guardrails OK`.\n\nCLI proof using an isolated state dir:\n\n```text\nOPENCLAW_DURABLE_WORKFLOWS=1 OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/private/tmp/openclaw-durable-pr-proof npm run openclaw -- durable stats --json\n{\n  \"path\": \"/private/tmp/openclaw-durable-pr-proof/state/openclaw.sqlite\",\n  \"runs\": 0,\n  \"events\": 0,\n  \"steps\": 0,\n  \"openRuns\": 0\n}\n```\n\nI also attempted a full `npm run build`; it reached `tsdown` and was interrupted after several minutes of no output. The source CLI runner rebuilt the needed runtime chunks successfully for the CLI proof above, and CI should provide the full build result.\n\n## Follow-Up PRs If This Boundary Is Accepted\n\n- Recovery worker and reconciliation loop.\n- Retention/compaction policy for durable events.\n- Upgrade/doctor/backup proof around the shared schema.\n- Task Flow and Workboard projections.\n- Multi-worker lease contention tests.\n",
        "branch": "codex/openclaw-durable-agent-coordination",
